<h1><i class="fa fa-cog"></i>Setting Your Desktop App</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/getting-started"><i class="fa fa-bicycle"></i>Getting Started</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-cog"></i>Setting Desktop App</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p>Sharedigm has the ability to show your most used apps on the desktop, similar to how multiple desktops can be defined in other operating systems. </p>
	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-desktop"></i>Switching Between Desktop Apps</h2>
			<p>You can change the current desktop app by clicking on the icons in the Desktop App control. You can also switch between desktop apps by clicking on the header bar or footer bar and dragging to the left or right. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-apps.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Desktop Apps"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-apps.png" style="width:150px" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Desktop Apps</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-cog"></i>Configuring Your Desktop Apps</h2>
			<p>You can optimize your <%= application.name %> user experience by placing the apps that you use most often on the desktop. The currently set of desktop apps are shown in the Desktop App control on the header bar. To change the <a href="#help/getting-started/using-desktop">Desktop</a> app, first click on the Settings icon on the header bar.  

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/settings-icon.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Settings Icon"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/settings-icon.png" style="width:300px" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Settings Icon</div>
			</div>

			<p>This will launch the <a href="#apps/settings-browser">Settings Browser</a> app.  Click on the "Desktop" icon. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/info/apps/settings-browser/settings-browser.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Settings Browser"><img class="dialog" src="images/info/apps/settings-browser/settings-browser.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Settings Browser</div>
			</div>

			<p>This will show the current desktop apps along with a set of buttons.  By clicking these buttons, you can add a desktop app, change the current desktop app or remove a desktop app. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-app-selector.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Desktop App Selector"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-app-selector.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Desktop App Selector</div>
			</div>

			<ol>
				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-rocket"></i></span>Apps</h3>
					<p>The <a href="#apps/app-launcher">App Launcher</a> allows quick and easy access to apps.  Showing the <a href="#apps/app-launcher">App Launcher</a> on the desktop is used most often on mobile platforms where quick and easy access to apps is a priority. </p>

					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-app-launcher.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Desktop App Launcher"><img src="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-app-launcher.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Desktop App Launcher</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-folder"></i></span>Files</h3>
					<p>The <a href="#apps/file-browser">File Browser</a> app allows files and folders to be viewed, organized, and shared.  This app is used as the primary desktop app by default and is used when access to files and data is a priority. </p>

					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-file-browser.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Desktop File Browser"><img src="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-file-browser.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Desktop File Browser</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-newspaper"></i></span>Messeges</h3>
					<p>The <a href="#apps/communicator"><%= config.apps['communicator'].name %></a> app allows you to read and write posts and direct messages with your friends and colleagues.  This mode is used most often by social media users or by office groups where communication and collaboration is a priority. </p>

					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-communicator.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Desktop <%= config.apps['communicator'].name %>"><img src="images/help/getting-started/setting-desktop-app/desktop-communicator.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Desktop <%= config.apps['communicator'].name %></div>
					</div>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</li>

	</ol>
</div>